data.title: Crytek UK Characters
data.meta_description: Formerly Free Radical Design, Crytek UK was a console-focused satellite studio for the Germany-based Crytek. The studio was shut down on July 30, 2014.
data.text:
Gingerbread Man

3

Gingerbread Man is a character in the TimeSpliiters games who is available only in Multiplayer.He is fondly remembered for his quote from TimeSplitters 3 "Bite my crunchy brown ass!" which he would say during character selection.

Harry Tipper

3

Harry Tipper is one of the few characters of the TimeSplitters series who has reprised his role in all three games. In TimeSplitters 2 and TimeSplitters Future Perfect he attempts to foil the evil plans of his arch-nemesis, Khallos.

Robofish

3

A fish in a bowl on top of a robot body, motivations and personality unknown.

Chastity

3

Chastity is a cop from the near future who appears in all three TimeSplitters games (though only in the story portions of the first two).

Captain Ash

3

Captain Ash is an adventurous old Scot from the TimeSplitters series. He also has the uncommon trait of appearing in all of the current TimeSplitters games.

Duckman Drake

3

A character that appears in all three Timesplitter games. He is an anthropomorphic duck who never appears in any of the games' stories, but he does have arcade challenges dedicated to him.

Jo-Beth Casey

3

Jo-Beth Casey is the younger sister of Mary-Beth, and makes a brief appearance in TimeSplitters 2. In TimeSplitters: Future Perfect, Jo-Beth was redesigned and given a much larger role as one of the games main supporting characters.

R-One-Oh-Seven

2

Featuring in both Timesplitters 2 and Future Perfect, R-One-Oh-Seven (previously Robert) is a human who believes he is a robot. He also responded to letters on Free Radical's official website until it was shut down.

Viola

2

Viola is a character in TimeSplitters 2 who is intent on destroying the necromancer, Jacque de la morte, in 1985 Paris.

Mr. Underwood

2

A posh, english myth buster, he has now teamed up with Viola to battle Jacque de la Morte.

Venus Starr

2

Venus Starr is a cowgirl remarkable for her large bust, who appears in TimeSplitters 2 and TimeSplitters: Future Perfect.

Handyman

2

The Handyman was created in the cheese-induced nightmares of gangster Hatchet Sal. These Handymen are the hands of Hatchet Sal's victims, which he kept under his bed as trophies.

Corporal Hart

2

In TimeSplitters 2, Corporal Hart, along with Sergeant Cortez, is one of two space marines sent to retrieve the time crystals from a space station that is under control by the Time Splitters.

Francis Peshy

1

Francis Peshy is a corporal in Mantel's forces in the first-person shooter, Haze. He was a star quarterback in high school but wasn't the sharpest tool in the shed.

Jed

1

Jed is a character from Timesplitters: Future Perfect. He is unlocked by getting a gold or better on all challenge matches.

INSETICK SD/10

1

A character in Timesplitters: Future Perfect. He can be unlocked by completing elite league with all golds or better.

Lola Varuska

1

Lola Varuska is an unlockable character in TimeSplitters 2. She is the trapeze artist in the Circus, and wears a light purple top accompanied by a skimpy thong-backed dress. Lola, during an earlier event, saved Bear from an animal trap before he became her pet. She's also known for her "dazzling smile".
